1
00:00:04,604 --> 00:00:08,308
<i>Your son shoplifted from my store.</i>

2
00:00:08,375 --> 00:00:10,744
We shouldn't let him manipulate us
any further.

3
00:00:10,810 --> 00:00:12,846
What is he demanding?

4
00:00:12,912 --> 00:00:15,615
<i>The victim is Hideyuki Sakuma,</i>
<i>40 years old.</i>

5
00:00:15,682 --> 00:00:18,284
The manager of Smile Sakuma
in Mitsuba Minami.

6
00:00:18,351 --> 00:00:20,053
<i>The bullet extracted from the body</i>

7
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:23,656
<i>was fired from the gun that belonged</i>
<i>to Keisuke's father.</i>

8
00:00:24,224 --> 00:00:27,627
<i>This will be a secret</i>
<i>between just the four of us.</i>

9
00:00:27,694 --> 00:00:30,230
One of us here opened the time capsule

10
00:00:30,296 --> 00:00:31,464
and took out that gun.

11
00:00:31,531 --> 00:00:34,934
<i>I didn't get home until around 11:00 p.m.</i>

12
00:00:35,001 --> 00:00:36,202
I opened the time capsule,

13
00:00:36,269 --> 00:00:38,338
- but there was no gun inside.
- Are you serious?

14
00:00:38,405 --> 00:00:40,407
The time capsule was opened two times.

15
00:00:40,473 --> 00:00:42,208
<i>If you’re telling the truth,</i>

16
00:00:42,275 --> 00:00:43,910
<i>it would have to be either Makiko</i>
<i>or Naoto.</i>

17
00:00:43,977 --> 00:00:46,312
It'll be all right, Maki.

18
00:00:49,816 --> 00:00:51,718
Nice to meet you. I'm Hiromi.

19
00:00:51,785 --> 00:00:52,886
Are you going to marry her?

20
00:00:54,687 --> 00:00:57,690
<i>But it is true</i>
<i>that there is some connection</i>

21
00:00:58,191 --> 00:01:01,828
<i>between this incident</i>
<i>and the incident from 23 years ago.</i>

22
00:01:02,929 --> 00:01:04,798
Please accompany me to the police station…

23
00:01:05,465 --> 00:01:07,901
- Mr. Naoto Sakuma.
- What?

24
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:11,704
You were captured on the security camera.

25
00:01:11,771 --> 00:01:15,442
It was possible for you to be
at the scene of the murder.

26
00:01:21,114 --> 00:01:23,550
Keisuke!

27
00:01:24,551 --> 00:01:26,653
Keisuke!

28
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:29,956
Keisuke!

29
00:01:42,469 --> 00:01:43,736
Nagai,

30
00:01:43,803 --> 00:01:45,371
- what's going on?
- Mr. Tobina.

31
00:01:46,372 --> 00:01:47,974
What are you doing, Ms. Nara?

32
00:01:49,209 --> 00:01:50,810
His alibi has fallen apart.

33
00:01:51,544 --> 00:01:54,481
Mr. Naoto Sakuma will voluntarily
accompany us to the station.

34
00:01:59,486 --> 00:02:00,487
I…

35
00:02:01,588 --> 00:02:02,489
will go too.

36
00:02:02,555 --> 00:02:04,457
Detective Tobina, you’re off duty today.

37
00:02:06,860 --> 00:02:08,728
What brings you here?

38
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:11,531
Getting together with your

39
00:02:11,598 --> 00:02:13,933
- classmates to discuss something?
- I'm off duty,

40
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:16,136
- so I came to hang out.
- I see.

41
00:02:16,202 --> 00:02:17,170
I'll be off then.

42
00:02:19,272 --> 00:02:20,340
Let's go.

43
00:02:29,549 --> 00:02:30,850
Naoto.

44
00:02:57,911 --> 00:03:00,013
Masaki. I'm coming in.

45
00:03:09,889 --> 00:03:11,157
Were they police officers?

46
00:03:12,859 --> 00:03:13,760
Yeah.

47
00:03:15,762 --> 00:03:17,430
They took Mr. Naoto with them?

48
00:03:18,298 --> 00:03:20,600
They just want to talk to him

49
00:03:21,334 --> 00:03:23,870
about his older brother, that’s all.

50
00:03:26,573 --> 00:03:28,675
How did they know that Naoto was here?

51
00:03:28,741 --> 00:03:30,510
Does that mean that he was being watched?

52
00:03:30,577 --> 00:03:33,813
- It would seem so.
- You didn’t know about this, Junichi?

53
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:36,349
I don’t think I was told
because I’m close with Naoto.

54
00:03:40,853 --> 00:03:42,855
But did Naoto really do it?

55
00:03:43,856 --> 00:03:45,925
If that's the case,
when did he dig up the time capsule?

56
00:03:49,128 --> 00:03:52,065
I opened the time capsule
around 9:00 p.m. on Friday night.

57
00:03:52,832 --> 00:03:55,668
The gun wasn't there at that time,
so it must have been removed before then.

58
00:03:58,938 --> 00:04:00,506
Do you think Naoto really did it?

59
00:04:03,042 --> 00:04:04,177
If he didn't do it,

60
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:06,946
why would he bother
to provide a false alibi?

61
00:04:10,850 --> 00:04:12,952
Maybe it's because of a woman?

62
00:04:13,453 --> 00:04:14,287
Huh?

63
00:04:14,354 --> 00:04:17,423
Maybe he’s secretly
dating someone complicated

64
00:04:18,191 --> 00:04:20,360
and wanted to hide the fact
that they were together.

65
00:04:20,426 --> 00:04:21,594
That’s probably not it.

66
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:24,597
Because he's always loved Makiko.

67
00:04:25,531 --> 00:04:29,202
I think he has always
had feelings for Makiko.

68
00:04:31,004 --> 00:04:33,006
Why didn't you talk back to them?

69
00:04:33,673 --> 00:04:35,308
It's so ridiculous.

70
00:04:36,009 --> 00:04:37,510
You're not going to do anything?

71
00:04:38,878 --> 00:04:40,346
- Come on, Naoto.
- What happened?

72
00:04:41,547 --> 00:04:44,517
Yanagihara and his friends
hid Naoto's shoes.

73
00:04:45,485 --> 00:04:48,388
They're in sixth grade,
and still doing things like that?

74
00:04:48,454 --> 00:04:49,789
They're so immature.

75
00:04:49,856 --> 00:04:52,792
Let’s all go home in our indoor shoes.

76
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:54,193
What?

77
00:04:54,260 --> 00:04:56,229
What are you saying?

78
00:04:56,929 --> 00:04:59,399
Junichi, Keisuke, go get his shoes back.

79
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:01,200
No, it’s all right.

80
00:05:01,701 --> 00:05:03,636
You guys can get them back, right?

81
00:05:06,172 --> 00:05:08,141
Yes, ma'am.

82
00:05:08,207 --> 00:05:09,709
- Fine, we'll go.
- This way.

83
00:05:09,776 --> 00:05:10,610
- Hurry.
- Yeah.

84
00:05:10,677 --> 00:05:11,711
All right.

85
00:05:12,278 --> 00:05:13,746
Get it back!

86
00:05:13,813 --> 00:05:14,714
Which way?

87
00:05:14,781 --> 00:05:16,015
Turn right.

88
00:05:19,585 --> 00:05:20,420
Hey.

89
00:05:22,388 --> 00:05:24,457
- What is it?
- Never mind.

90
00:05:24,524 --> 00:05:26,392
Stop that. What is it?

91
00:05:26,959 --> 00:05:29,228
Whatever it is you know, just tell me.

92
00:05:32,565 --> 00:05:36,536
When Hideyuki Sakuma contacted Makiko
about Masaki's shoplifting incident,

93
00:05:37,236 --> 00:05:39,372
she tried to contact Naoto
to ask for advice

94
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:41,040
and sent him messages and left voicemails.

95
00:05:42,775 --> 00:05:46,012
Naoto forgot his smartphone in Japan
while on a business trip overseas,

96
00:05:47,146 --> 00:05:48,414
and he must have found out

97
00:05:49,115 --> 00:05:50,717
about the shoplifting after he came back.

98
00:05:52,852 --> 00:05:55,822
So you think he went
to his brother's place to discuss that?

99
00:06:02,161 --> 00:06:03,930
- This way.
<i>- I'm sorry,</i>

100
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:05,598
<i>but I need to talk to you about something.</i>

101
00:06:05,665 --> 00:06:06,499
MAKIKO IWAMOTO

102
00:06:07,333 --> 00:06:10,169
<i>Masaki shoplifted</i>
<i>from your older brother's supermarket.</i>

103
00:06:12,171 --> 00:06:15,141
<i>Maki, I'm sorry for not getting back</i>
<i>to your messages and calls.</i>

104
00:06:15,908 --> 00:06:18,344
I forgot my smartphone
and went on a business trip.

105
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:21,981
<i>Sorry to bother you when you’re busy.</i>

106
00:06:22,482 --> 00:06:24,650
No, I'm sorry too,

107
00:06:25,618 --> 00:06:29,288
about my brother causing you trouble.

108
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:31,224
<i>What happened?</i>

109
00:06:32,759 --> 00:06:35,895
<i>We gave him the money yesterday.</i>

110
00:06:35,962 --> 00:06:37,930
What? How much?

111
00:06:38,798 --> 00:06:39,932
<i>300,000 yen.</i>

112
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:44,537
I'm really sorry.

113
00:06:45,872 --> 00:06:48,975
<i>I'll talk to my brother.</i>

114
00:06:50,376 --> 00:06:51,611
<i>Okay.</i>

115
00:06:51,677 --> 00:06:52,979
<i>Thank you.</i>

116
00:06:55,314 --> 00:06:56,349
<i>Naoto…</i>

117
00:06:58,951 --> 00:07:00,119
It'll be all right.

118
00:07:01,721 --> 00:07:02,588
<i>Okay.</i>

119
00:07:10,029 --> 00:07:12,265
<i>If Naoto had used that gun,</i>

120
00:07:12,331 --> 00:07:14,700
he'd be asked where he got it from, right?

121
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:17,103
Knowing him…

122
00:07:17,837 --> 00:07:22,608
Yeah, he probably won’t talk about the gun
or the time capsule.

123
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:27,246
Even so, Ms. Nara might still uncover
the truth anyway.

124
00:07:32,018 --> 00:07:32,985
Junichi,

125
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:35,555
will you be all right?

126
00:07:35,621 --> 00:07:36,656
What do you mean?

127
00:07:38,057 --> 00:07:39,192
You’re a detective,

128
00:07:39,692 --> 00:07:42,128
but you didn't tell the police
that we buried that gun,

129
00:07:42,195 --> 00:07:44,297
and you leaked information to us.

130
00:07:44,797 --> 00:07:46,766
This is no time to be laughing.

131
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:50,236
If that gets discovered, won't you lose
your badge or even face a penalty?

132
00:07:53,072 --> 00:07:54,607
Don’t worry about me.

133
00:07:56,342 --> 00:07:58,110
Either way, there's no turning back now.

134
00:08:02,515 --> 00:08:03,649
I'm going to the station now.

135
00:08:04,517 --> 00:08:05,451
I’ll

136
00:08:06,719 --> 00:08:07,920
stay by Makiko’s side.

137
00:08:09,856 --> 00:08:11,390
Is your wife okay?

138
00:08:11,457 --> 00:08:13,259
She knows I’m staying in Mitsuba tonight.

139
00:08:16,729 --> 00:08:18,598
Junichi is going to the station.

140
00:08:23,769 --> 00:08:24,604
Bye.

141
00:08:34,747 --> 00:08:36,682
Are you okay? You should rest.

142
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:38,885
Yeah.

143
00:08:42,655 --> 00:08:45,458
Are you blaming yourself for telling Naoto
about the shoplifting?

144
00:08:58,804 --> 00:08:59,805
<i>Naoto.</i>

145
00:09:09,181 --> 00:09:10,516
<i>He’s maintaining his silence?</i>

146
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:13,119
He’s here voluntarily,

147
00:09:13,185 --> 00:09:16,689
so if he continues to remain silent,
we’ll have to let him go soon.

148
00:09:31,137 --> 00:09:32,138
Mr. Sakuma,

149
00:09:33,472 --> 00:09:34,540
are you hungry?

150
00:09:37,343 --> 00:09:39,779
Would you like to eat
a late-night snack with me?

151
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:43,716
Yes,

152
00:09:43,783 --> 00:09:46,919
I'm asking if you want to eat
because I’m the one who’s hungry.

153
00:09:50,723 --> 00:09:52,358
Or would you like to leave?

154
00:09:53,492 --> 00:09:55,595
Because you can leave too.

155
00:09:59,899 --> 00:10:02,401
As for the late-night snack,
we have instant ramen.

156
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:05,438
The available flavors are miso,

157
00:10:06,138 --> 00:10:09,709
soy sauce, salt, and curry.

158
00:10:11,243 --> 00:10:13,512
I listed them in my order of preference.

159
00:10:16,349 --> 00:10:17,650
Should I repeat it?

160
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:20,386
Miso,

161
00:10:21,420 --> 00:10:22,254
soy sauce,

162
00:10:23,422 --> 00:10:24,290
salt…

163
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:26,225
I did it.

164
00:10:31,430 --> 00:10:33,499
I killed my older brother.

165
00:10:39,138 --> 00:10:40,439
Hello.

166
00:10:40,506 --> 00:10:42,875
<i>That’s a long game of mahjong.</i>

167
00:10:43,809 --> 00:10:45,044
Sorry for not contacting you.

168
00:10:45,745 --> 00:10:48,147
<i>- I’m at the station.</i>
- Oh, I'm glad.

169
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:50,349
<i>Why are you glad?</i>

170
00:10:51,884 --> 00:10:53,285
I’m just glad

171
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:56,455
you’re not dead on the streets somewhere.

172
00:10:57,957 --> 00:10:59,091
Why would I be dead?

173
00:10:59,792 --> 00:11:03,996
<i>But someone who’s healthy</i>
<i>can suddenly collapse, you know.</i>

174
00:11:04,063 --> 00:11:05,297
I guess so.

175
00:11:06,065 --> 00:11:08,501
<i>I wonder if you think that way</i>
<i>because you’re a nurse.</i>

176
00:11:10,369 --> 00:11:11,604
More like,

177
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:14,607
because you’re a detective,

178
00:11:15,107 --> 00:11:18,077
who knows when or what kind
of trouble you might get involved in.

179
00:11:19,979 --> 00:11:21,681
I’ll always call if I can't make it home.

180
00:11:22,648 --> 00:11:25,051
<i>Yeah. To confirm you’re alive.</i>

181
00:11:26,385 --> 00:11:27,286
Yeah.

182
00:11:28,487 --> 00:11:31,390
<i>- Work hard.</i>
- Yeah. Bye.

183
00:11:34,293 --> 00:11:35,594
Detective Tobina.

184
00:11:36,629 --> 00:11:39,298
Mr. Naoto Sakuma
just confessed to the crime.

185
00:11:40,066 --> 00:11:43,536
He'll be staying here tonight,
and we'll question him in the morning.

186
00:11:43,602 --> 00:11:45,204
But since you were his classmate,

187
00:11:45,271 --> 00:11:47,306
you will not be allowed to join
the questioning.

188
00:12:43,262 --> 00:12:45,264
You can’t sleep?

189
00:12:47,099 --> 00:12:48,267
You scared me.

190
00:12:50,603 --> 00:12:52,772
Of course you can't fall asleep, huh?

191
00:12:53,572 --> 00:12:56,542
After all, your former classmate
just confessed to murder.

192
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:02,948
When and where did he obtain the gun

193
00:13:03,482 --> 00:13:06,085
used to shoot Hideyuki Sakuma,

194
00:13:06,585 --> 00:13:09,755
and where was he keeping it?

195
00:13:10,689 --> 00:13:17,229
There’s no way he took the gun
when he discovered the body

196
00:13:17,296 --> 00:13:19,899
of Officer Kiyohara

197
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:22,968
23 years ago, right?

198
00:13:23,903 --> 00:13:27,540
Because if that were the case,
you would have known.

199
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:31,877
Are you listening?

200
00:13:35,014 --> 00:13:36,081
Yes.

201
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:37,683
Um…

202
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:40,019
isn’t it awkward to talk
with your eye mask on?

203
00:13:40,753 --> 00:13:44,290
I don’t have much of a beauty regime.

204
00:13:44,356 --> 00:13:46,392
Beauty what?

205
00:13:46,458 --> 00:13:47,927
I said,

206
00:13:48,427 --> 00:13:50,996
- a beauty regime.
- Yes, I see.

207
00:13:51,063 --> 00:13:54,834
However, there's one thing I always do.

208
00:13:55,868 --> 00:13:56,869
At night,

209
00:13:57,369 --> 00:14:00,439
I always remove my makeup
before going to bed.

210
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:01,874
Therefore, the eye mask.

211
00:14:02,374 --> 00:14:04,343
You're wearing it
because you have no makeup on?

212
00:14:04,977 --> 00:14:05,845
Good night.

213
00:14:14,453 --> 00:14:15,421
Huh?

214
00:14:18,457 --> 00:14:19,625
Is she serious?

215
00:14:20,893 --> 00:14:22,728
Oh man, she woke me up.

216
00:14:24,029 --> 00:14:25,231
Oh jeez.

217
00:14:26,465 --> 00:14:28,367
I probably can’t go back to sleep anymore.

218
00:14:30,269 --> 00:14:32,037
That's insane.

219
00:14:32,104 --> 00:14:35,741
MITSUBA POLICE STATION

220
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:48,721
On Saturday, the day of the incident,

221
00:14:48,787 --> 00:14:52,157
we have confirmed
that you arrived at Haneda Airport

222
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:53,659
at 8:55 p.m.

223
00:14:53,726 --> 00:14:55,160
NAOTO SAKUMA

224
00:14:55,227 --> 00:14:57,029
What did you do after that?

225
00:14:57,096 --> 00:15:00,599
I stopped by my brother's office
at the supermarket.

226
00:15:02,167 --> 00:15:03,269
Why did you go there?

227
00:15:03,836 --> 00:15:05,738
My brother was a manager in name only,

228
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:09,208
and he had a bad reputation among
the employees, so it worried me a lot.

229
00:15:09,775 --> 00:15:11,944
So I was anxious about whether my brother

230
00:15:12,011 --> 00:15:14,880
actually did his job
while I was away on a business trip.

231
00:15:14,947 --> 00:15:16,081
Then?

232
00:15:18,784 --> 00:15:20,753
He asked me to lend him money.

233
00:15:20,819 --> 00:15:22,054
What did you think about that?

234
00:15:22,888 --> 00:15:24,189
I thought, "Again?"

235
00:15:24,256 --> 00:15:26,125
"Enough of this already."

236
00:15:26,191 --> 00:15:29,662
How many times have you lent money
to your older brother?

237
00:15:29,728 --> 00:15:31,330
It happened so many times

238
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:33,399
I can't remember the exact number.

239
00:15:34,266 --> 00:15:36,535
Did you give him money this time too?

240
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:38,470
When I took money out of my wallet,

241
00:15:38,537 --> 00:15:41,073
he said it wasn't enough and told me
to go back home to get more.

242
00:15:41,140 --> 00:15:43,075
How much did he say he wanted?

243
00:15:43,876 --> 00:15:45,177
One million.

244
00:15:45,811 --> 00:15:48,213
He said he had to make payment
for his debts.

245
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:49,581
Then what happened?

246
00:15:51,717 --> 00:15:54,553
I was initially going to do as he said,

247
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:56,021
so I got in my car.

248
00:15:57,423 --> 00:15:59,058
But then I changed my mind.

249
00:16:00,225 --> 00:16:02,461
I was tired from my business trip,

250
00:16:03,529 --> 00:16:05,064
so I went back to the office instead.

251
00:16:07,599 --> 00:16:09,001
My brother got angry

252
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:11,670
and started throwing things at me.

253
00:16:13,305 --> 00:16:14,807
That led to an argument,

254
00:16:15,908 --> 00:16:17,509
and my brother took a gun

255
00:16:18,377 --> 00:16:19,878
from underneath the couch.

256
00:16:21,347 --> 00:16:25,050
<i>Your brother took out a gun</i>
<i>from underneath the couch?</i>

257
00:16:25,117 --> 00:16:26,085
Yes.

258
00:16:26,585 --> 00:16:28,387
<i>Weren't you scared?</i>

259
00:16:28,454 --> 00:16:31,156
I was pretty sure my brother
wouldn't actually pull the trigger.

260
00:16:31,657 --> 00:16:33,192
I figured it was just a threat.

261
00:16:34,526 --> 00:16:35,461
Then?

262
00:16:36,996 --> 00:16:38,664
I grabbed the muzzle of the gun

263
00:16:40,766 --> 00:16:43,569
and we started fighting.

264
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:46,238
A fight…

265
00:16:48,173 --> 00:16:49,975
<i>A struggle over the gun broke out</i>

266
00:16:50,909 --> 00:16:52,845
<i>near the office entrance.</i>

267
00:16:54,847 --> 00:16:59,018
<i>My brother wasn't as strong as I expected.</i>

268
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:03,422
Perhaps it was because he was drunk.

269
00:17:04,456 --> 00:17:05,424
And then…

270
00:17:09,161 --> 00:17:10,396
<i>There was a loud bang,</i>

271
00:17:12,131 --> 00:17:15,601
<i>and blood started coming out</i>
<i>of my brother's abdomen.</i>

272
00:17:17,636 --> 00:17:18,737
Where was the gun?

273
00:17:19,571 --> 00:17:20,506
In my hand.

274
00:17:25,778 --> 00:17:27,479
You pulled the trigger?

275
00:17:30,349 --> 00:17:33,018
I don't remember clearly
what happened at that moment,

276
00:17:35,487 --> 00:17:36,822
but yes, I think I did.

277
00:17:37,923 --> 00:17:42,861
Didn't you think
to call the police or an ambulance?

278
00:17:45,798 --> 00:17:48,834
I honestly don't remember much,

279
00:17:50,202 --> 00:17:52,471
but I think I was unable to move
for a while.

280
00:17:57,443 --> 00:17:59,645
<i>By the time I realized,</i>
<i>there was a pool of blood,</i>

281
00:18:01,814 --> 00:18:03,682
and I knew he was dead.

282
00:18:04,483 --> 00:18:05,517
Then what did you do?

283
00:18:06,318 --> 00:18:07,719
I ran away.

284
00:18:08,887 --> 00:18:09,855
What about the gun?

285
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:12,691
I took it with me.

286
00:18:18,664 --> 00:18:20,365
Did you already know

287
00:18:20,432 --> 00:18:23,735
from before the incident
that your brother owned a gun?

288
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:27,806
Yes, but more like,

289
00:18:27,873 --> 00:18:30,742
I thought it was fake.
I didn’t think it was a real gun.

290
00:18:32,044 --> 00:18:33,679
Can you explain that in detail?

291
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:37,916
I think it was when
I was in middle school.

292
00:18:39,017 --> 00:18:42,888
I went into my brother's room
without permission and saw a gun.

293
00:18:44,256 --> 00:18:46,792
I thought it was a toy gun
and tried to touch it,

294
00:18:47,593 --> 00:18:49,628
but I got caught by my brother
who had just come home,

295
00:18:50,596 --> 00:18:52,197
and he got very angry with me.

296
00:18:52,865 --> 00:18:55,501
Did you tell anyone about the gun?

297
00:18:56,935 --> 00:18:57,903
No.

298
00:18:58,837 --> 00:19:01,673
My brother was bragging,
saying it was the real thing,

299
00:19:02,174 --> 00:19:03,575
but I thought he was lying.

300
00:19:05,744 --> 00:19:09,014
Did he say where he found the gun?

301
00:19:12,084 --> 00:19:14,186
He said he found it

302
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:15,654
in the forest.

303
00:19:19,024 --> 00:19:20,526
Is this the same forest

304
00:19:21,193 --> 00:19:23,929
where you and your classmates
were the first to discover

305
00:19:23,996 --> 00:19:26,865
the body of Officer Kazuo Kiyohara?

306
00:19:28,534 --> 00:19:30,369
I think so,

307
00:19:30,435 --> 00:19:32,905
but I don't know the details.
I only heard that it was a forest.

308
00:19:37,809 --> 00:19:38,710
So then,

309
00:19:40,345 --> 00:19:41,947
where is that gun

310
00:19:42,748 --> 00:19:44,082
right now?

311
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:52,524
Where is that gun right now?

312
00:19:54,526 --> 00:19:57,095
I threw it away. In the river.

313
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:02,334
He stated that he threw away the gun
in this area.

314
00:20:02,401 --> 00:20:04,102
Recovering the gun is top priority.

315
00:20:04,169 --> 00:20:07,072
Increase the search personnel
and conduct a thorough search,

316
00:20:07,139 --> 00:20:10,542
intensify the search for any witnesses,
and make sure you find it.

317
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:12,211
Yes, sir!

318
00:20:14,179 --> 00:20:16,949
You left your brother's office

319
00:20:17,015 --> 00:20:19,518
and stopped at a gas station
to put in gas on your way home.

320
00:20:20,352 --> 00:20:21,954
Is that correct?

321
00:20:22,688 --> 00:20:24,790
My memory is a little hazy,

322
00:20:26,024 --> 00:20:28,527
but by the time I realized,
I was driving on the highway

323
00:20:29,595 --> 00:20:32,030
and saw that the gas lamp was on.

324
00:20:32,531 --> 00:20:34,967
I stopped at the first gas station I saw.

325
00:20:36,535 --> 00:20:40,272
Now let's fast forward
to the day after the incident.

326
00:20:41,306 --> 00:20:44,943
You stated that you had received
a threatening letter.

327
00:20:45,010 --> 00:20:47,212
It said that if we proceed
with the construction

328
00:20:47,279 --> 00:20:52,584
of the building complex
that our company is planning,

329
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:55,287
divine punishment will befall us.

330
00:20:55,854 --> 00:20:57,222
Was that true?

331
00:20:57,889 --> 00:21:00,325
No, that was a lie.

332
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:04,830
I wanted to divert suspicion away
from myself, even just a little,

333
00:21:05,330 --> 00:21:07,132
so I made up that story.

334
00:21:19,745 --> 00:21:20,846
Maki.

335
00:21:21,546 --> 00:21:22,481
Mrs. Sakuma.

336
00:21:23,582 --> 00:21:24,650
Naoto…

337
00:21:26,385 --> 00:21:27,252
Naoto…

338
00:21:27,319 --> 00:21:29,321
got arrested.

339
00:21:51,443 --> 00:21:52,911
- Nagai.
- Yes?

340
00:21:54,846 --> 00:21:57,683
Just give me one moment alone
with Naoto Sakuma.

341
00:21:58,183 --> 00:22:00,018
- What?
- I won’t cause trouble for you.

342
00:22:00,085 --> 00:22:02,587
I can't do that.

343
00:22:02,654 --> 00:22:04,723
- What are you going to do?
- I just want to talk to him.

344
00:22:05,490 --> 00:22:07,559
- I can’t.
- There are things that only I can ask him.

345
00:22:07,626 --> 00:22:08,927
This is not a good idea.

346
00:22:09,428 --> 00:22:11,430
Please. Just give me one minute.

347
00:22:13,999 --> 00:22:14,866
Please.

348
00:22:16,735 --> 00:22:20,205
- If it's 30 seconds…
- Okay.

349
00:22:20,272 --> 00:22:22,708
- Are you serious?
- It's a deal.

350
00:22:25,077 --> 00:22:27,913
I threw the gun away right here.

351
00:22:27,979 --> 00:22:29,414
Which way?

352
00:22:29,481 --> 00:22:32,284
This is no joke.

353
00:22:32,351 --> 00:22:33,852
Will we be able to find it?

354
00:22:38,857 --> 00:22:40,826
Ready.

355
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:43,595
Thank you.

356
00:22:54,706 --> 00:22:55,674
Naoto.

357
00:22:58,777 --> 00:23:00,112
Did you really do it?

358
00:23:02,414 --> 00:23:03,248
Yeah.

359
00:23:04,983 --> 00:23:07,219
- Let me ask just one thing.
- It's okay,

360
00:23:08,186 --> 00:23:10,589
I said that my brother
found the gun in the forest.

361
00:23:12,958 --> 00:23:15,360
I haven’t mentioned the time capsule,

362
00:23:15,894 --> 00:23:17,562
and I’ll never mention it in the future.

363
00:23:18,930 --> 00:23:20,098
The gun will most likely

364
00:23:20,766 --> 00:23:23,568
- never appear ever again.
- What I want to know is,

365
00:23:24,569 --> 00:23:27,672
when exactly did you take the gun
out of the time capsule?

366
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:34,112
Thirty-seven, thirty-eight,

367
00:23:34,713 --> 00:23:36,515
thirty-nine, forty.

368
00:23:36,581 --> 00:23:38,016
I gave ten bonus seconds.

369
00:23:50,796 --> 00:23:52,030
Ms. Iwamoto.

370
00:23:57,869 --> 00:23:59,304
What brings you here today?

371
00:23:59,971 --> 00:24:03,942
Mr. Naoto Sakuma’s mother asked me
to drop off his change of clothes.

372
00:24:04,009 --> 00:24:05,510
I see.

373
00:24:07,012 --> 00:24:10,515
I'm sure you're worried
about Mr. Naoto Sakuma.

374
00:24:11,583 --> 00:24:12,417
Yes.

375
00:24:12,918 --> 00:24:15,787
As you know, I can't talk about the status
of the investigation.

376
00:24:17,789 --> 00:24:18,623
Yes.

377
00:24:18,690 --> 00:24:20,158
Oh?

378
00:24:20,892 --> 00:24:22,828
Surely, Detective Tobina hasn't been

379
00:24:22,894 --> 00:24:26,665
leaking details of the investigation
to his former classmates, right?

380
00:24:27,732 --> 00:24:28,667
Of course not.

381
00:24:28,733 --> 00:24:31,136
Please don't take it so seriously.
I'm just kidding.

382
00:24:33,572 --> 00:24:34,806
May I see Naoto?

383
00:24:35,674 --> 00:24:36,675
Huh?

384
00:24:37,742 --> 00:24:38,777
I’m just kidding.

385
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:43,248
I’m sorry.

386
00:24:46,318 --> 00:24:47,419
Interesting.

387
00:24:49,387 --> 00:24:51,323
You can go inside to drop those off.

388
00:24:51,389 --> 00:24:52,457
Okay.

389
00:24:52,524 --> 00:24:55,393
MITSUBA POLICE STATION

390
00:25:27,492 --> 00:25:28,927
She got to see him after all.

391
00:25:32,330 --> 00:25:34,733
It was brought in by a person
named Ms. Makiko Iwamoto.

392
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:37,269
We'll have it processed later.

393
00:25:47,946 --> 00:25:49,214
<i>Naoto!</i>

394
00:25:52,584 --> 00:25:53,418
Maki!

395
00:25:54,185 --> 00:25:57,455
Naoto, long time no see.

396
00:25:57,522 --> 00:25:58,657
It's been a while.

397
00:25:59,357 --> 00:26:02,561
- What? You quit kendo?
- Yeah.

398
00:26:02,627 --> 00:26:04,029
Why?

399
00:26:04,629 --> 00:26:07,666
I became friends with a girl who sat
next to me at the entrance ceremony,

400
00:26:07,732 --> 00:26:09,467
and she invited me
to join the basketball club.

401
00:26:09,968 --> 00:26:12,837
That's a shame
since you were so good at kendo.

402
00:26:12,904 --> 00:26:14,539
I’m good at basketball too.

403
00:26:14,606 --> 00:26:17,375
I'm the only second-year student
on the roster.

404
00:26:17,442 --> 00:26:18,677
I expect no less from you, Maki.

405
00:26:19,177 --> 00:26:21,846
You were always competing
with Junichi and Keisuke,

406
00:26:21,913 --> 00:26:24,249
so playing basketball against girls
must be a piece of cake.

407
00:26:25,283 --> 00:26:27,619
Hey, have you been in contact
with those two?

408
00:26:28,420 --> 00:26:29,588
No,

409
00:26:29,654 --> 00:26:32,257
not at all ever since
we graduated elementary school.

410
00:26:33,925 --> 00:26:36,628
Both Junichi and Keisuke are heartless.

411
00:26:40,065 --> 00:26:41,132
Would it be okay

412
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:45,770
if I went to cheer you on
at your next basketball game?

413
00:26:46,271 --> 00:26:48,840
I’ll be too embarrassed.

414
00:26:49,908 --> 00:26:51,910
I mean, I go to an all-girls school.

415
00:26:51,977 --> 00:26:54,913
If you came to cheer me on,
rumors would spread like wildfire.

416
00:26:57,115 --> 00:26:58,783
That's true.

417
00:26:59,751 --> 00:27:00,752
Oh, but I guess

418
00:27:00,819 --> 00:27:03,655
it would be less troublesome
if I just say that you’re my boyfriend.

419
00:27:05,490 --> 00:27:09,060
Hey, if it isn’t my younger brother.

420
00:27:12,163 --> 00:27:14,799
Hey, man, I just lost some money
playing pachinko.

421
00:27:20,238 --> 00:27:22,307
You only have 3,000 yen?

422
00:27:22,374 --> 00:27:23,742
Stop that.

423
00:27:23,808 --> 00:27:26,411
Give that back. It’s Naoto’s.

424
00:27:27,779 --> 00:27:29,447
Wait, are you Iwamoto?

425
00:27:30,415 --> 00:27:33,818
You’ve gotten even more bratty
since I last saw you.

426
00:27:39,257 --> 00:27:40,592
How dare you!

427
00:28:05,050 --> 00:28:06,384
Naoto.

428
00:28:07,952 --> 00:28:09,187
Maki.

429
00:28:09,254 --> 00:28:12,057
I didn’t expect to see you here.

430
00:28:12,123 --> 00:28:13,725
I'm doing some shopping.

431
00:28:13,792 --> 00:28:15,627
I thought I'd walk around here
for a change.

432
00:28:15,694 --> 00:28:16,561
What about you, Maki?

433
00:28:16,628 --> 00:28:18,963
I was shopping too.
I needed light bulbs for the shop.

434
00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:19,964
I see.

435
00:28:22,300 --> 00:28:25,136
- You seem to be doing well.
- Yeah. You too.

436
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:28,139
What grade is Masaki in now?

437
00:28:28,206 --> 00:28:32,043
He's in third grade now.
He's such a handful.

438
00:28:32,544 --> 00:28:35,146
Hearing that you have a child
in third grade,

439
00:28:35,213 --> 00:28:37,682
makes me realize how old I've gotten.

440
00:28:38,183 --> 00:28:40,151
Why don't you get married too, Naoto?

441
00:28:41,086 --> 00:28:44,222
Although it must be strange coming from me
who got divorced.

442
00:28:44,923 --> 00:28:48,393
- Isn't there a nice girl in your life?
- There's no one like that.

443
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:51,763
- Really?
- I definitely don't have anyone.

444
00:28:52,530 --> 00:28:54,899
You don’t have to get
so worked up about it.

445
00:28:54,966 --> 00:28:56,901
You're right.

446
00:28:57,669 --> 00:28:58,870
Hey.

447
00:28:58,937 --> 00:29:02,040
Naoto, isn't your hair
getting a little long?

448
00:29:04,075 --> 00:29:07,312
I guess I haven't gotten it cut
in a while.

449
00:29:09,514 --> 00:29:11,249
Have you been that busy?

450
00:29:12,684 --> 00:29:15,120
I've been entrusted
with more responsibilities,

451
00:29:15,186 --> 00:29:18,123
and I became
the managing director this year.

452
00:29:18,189 --> 00:29:21,126
Wow! That's amazing!

453
00:29:23,361 --> 00:29:26,197
Do you have time to spare right now?
I'll cut your hair.

454
00:29:26,264 --> 00:29:27,599
- You're going to cut it?
- Yeah.

455
00:29:28,233 --> 00:29:30,802
I'll give you a hairstyle
that girls will fall for.

456
00:29:31,736 --> 00:29:32,704
What do you say?

457
00:29:37,976 --> 00:29:39,177
- Give me one second.
- Yeah.

458
00:29:41,646 --> 00:29:44,716
RE: HERE ARE THE MATERIALS
FOR TODAY'S MEETING

459
00:29:44,783 --> 00:29:47,752
I WILL BE A LITTLE LATE FOR THE MEETING
PLEASE START IT WITHOUT ME

460
00:29:47,819 --> 00:29:48,887
SEND

461
00:29:50,388 --> 00:29:52,090
I'll take you up on your offer.

462
00:29:52,157 --> 00:29:54,159
All right. Leave it up to me.

463
00:29:55,627 --> 00:29:57,195
I'll make you look the part.

464
00:29:57,262 --> 00:29:59,564
- Like a managing director?
- Yeah.

465
00:29:59,631 --> 00:30:02,500
<i>- Don't give me a weird hair style.</i>
<i>- How about we do this…?</i>

466
00:30:06,905 --> 00:30:09,641
<i>Did you receive the notice</i>
<i>about the reunion?</i>

467
00:30:10,675 --> 00:30:12,076
- Elementary school reunion?
- Yeah.

468
00:30:13,478 --> 00:30:14,813
Are you going?

469
00:30:15,413 --> 00:30:19,284
I haven't decided yet. What about you?

470
00:30:20,585 --> 00:30:23,221
I'm really busy with work,

471
00:30:23,755 --> 00:30:25,657
but I'll go if you're going.

472
00:30:29,627 --> 00:30:30,829
Do you think he'll come?

473
00:30:32,197 --> 00:30:33,298
Junichi?

474
00:30:33,798 --> 00:30:34,766
Yeah.

475
00:30:37,101 --> 00:30:40,305
Apparently, he's on a list of people
whose contact details are unknown.

476
00:30:41,706 --> 00:30:42,874
I see.

477
00:30:44,809 --> 00:30:47,078
Knowing Junichi, he must be doing fine.

478
00:30:48,479 --> 00:30:49,581
You're right.

479
00:31:05,029 --> 00:31:07,198
- It's raining already.
- Oh no.

480
00:31:07,265 --> 00:31:09,801
- I'll be going.
- Take care.

481
00:31:22,113 --> 00:31:22,947
Junichi?

482
00:31:23,014 --> 00:31:23,982
Yeah.

483
00:31:25,216 --> 00:31:27,118
<i>I'm glad you called.</i>

484
00:31:28,119 --> 00:31:31,656
<i>I figured it would be best to avoid</i>
<i>meeting in person,</i>

485
00:31:32,557 --> 00:31:35,126
<i>but I wasn't sure if it was okay to call.</i>

486
00:31:37,528 --> 00:31:39,664
Naoto confessed that he did it.

487
00:31:43,101 --> 00:31:45,236
<i>His brother asked for money,</i>
<i>they got into an argument…</i>

488
00:31:47,505 --> 00:31:49,774
<i>and during the struggle, the gun went off.</i>

489
00:31:51,743 --> 00:31:54,412
He testified that his brother
found the gun in the forest.

490
00:31:55,246 --> 00:31:58,983
<i>He said his brother found the gun</i>
<i>in the forest?</i>

491
00:32:00,985 --> 00:32:01,920
Yeah.

492
00:32:03,922 --> 00:32:07,792
To keep our time capsule a secret?

493
00:32:13,031 --> 00:32:15,633
How did Naoto come up with such a story?

494
00:32:18,903 --> 00:32:19,837
But…

495
00:32:22,206 --> 00:32:25,376
There are no loopholes in that story?

496
00:32:28,346 --> 00:32:30,181
No inconsistency has been found.

497
00:32:37,522 --> 00:32:39,290
In hindsight,

498
00:32:40,091 --> 00:32:42,527
I shouldn't have gone along with you.

499
00:32:44,896 --> 00:32:47,899
<i>I wish I had never gone to the forest.</i>

500
00:32:52,904 --> 00:32:55,907
I didn't even care to see
any freshwater crab.

501
00:33:01,379 --> 00:33:02,547
<i>Can you come here?</i>

502
00:33:06,017 --> 00:33:08,987
<i>Please come here right now, Junichi.</i>

503
00:33:12,857 --> 00:33:13,791
<i>Sorry,</i>

504
00:33:14,492 --> 00:33:16,661
<i>I just don't know what to do.</i>

505
00:33:27,572 --> 00:33:28,806
<i>I'll stay on the line</i>

506
00:33:30,942 --> 00:33:32,076
<i>until you've calmed down.</i>

507
00:33:37,348 --> 00:33:38,449
<i>I won't hang up.</i>

508
00:34:01,172 --> 00:34:02,240
Thank you.

509
00:34:05,443 --> 00:34:06,411
I'll hang up now.

510
00:34:09,147 --> 00:34:10,114
<i>Bye.</i>

511
00:34:39,744 --> 00:34:41,112
I see.

512
00:34:42,713 --> 00:34:45,083
Thanks for coming all the way to Tokyo
to leak information.

513
00:34:47,518 --> 00:34:50,455
- There's no turning back now.
- But I wonder…

514
00:34:52,857 --> 00:34:54,158
what Naoto's intention was

515
00:34:54,225 --> 00:34:57,361
when he went to his brother's place
with a gun that night?

516
00:35:00,832 --> 00:35:04,135
Of course, I don't think he went there
intending to shoot him.

517
00:35:04,202 --> 00:35:05,103
Keisuke,

518
00:35:06,704 --> 00:35:08,439
I asked to meet with you today

519
00:35:08,973 --> 00:35:10,174
to confirm something.

520
00:35:10,741 --> 00:35:11,576
What is it?

521
00:35:12,076 --> 00:35:15,947
You dug up the time capsule
around 9:00 p.m. on Friday, right?

522
00:35:16,514 --> 00:35:17,381
Yeah.

523
00:35:18,282 --> 00:35:19,951
You had an eyewitness testimony, right?

524
00:35:20,017 --> 00:35:22,019
The gun was already missing at that point.

525
00:35:23,721 --> 00:35:26,390
- You're sure about that?
- Yes, I'm sure.

526
00:35:27,959 --> 00:35:29,527
Why are you asking?

527
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:44,208
What is it, so late at night?

528
00:35:44,275 --> 00:35:46,310
The only one being detained tonight
is Naoto Sakuma, right?

529
00:35:46,377 --> 00:35:47,145
Yes.

530
00:35:47,712 --> 00:35:49,213
I want to talk with him.

531
00:35:49,981 --> 00:35:51,182
Privately.

532
00:35:55,653 --> 00:35:56,754
You're saying

533
00:35:57,255 --> 00:35:59,657
that you don't want this
to go on the record?

534
00:36:00,291 --> 00:36:01,225
Yes.

535
00:36:02,527 --> 00:36:04,128
I'd like you to step out as well.

536
00:36:04,195 --> 00:36:07,331
I can't allow that.
It's a violation of the rules.

537
00:36:07,398 --> 00:36:08,866
Can you please make an exception?

538
00:36:08,933 --> 00:36:11,102
You need to stop.
Or I'll report you to my superiors.

539
00:36:16,707 --> 00:36:19,377
You know, Mr. Konno, I play mahjong.

540
00:36:20,945 --> 00:36:22,947
Do you know of the mahjong parlor
in Nishimatsu?

541
00:36:24,081 --> 00:36:25,716
Sorry, we're full right now.

542
00:36:25,783 --> 00:36:27,718
A spot will open in about 15 minutes.

543
00:36:32,256 --> 00:36:35,960
- It seems like you won big money today.
- I was just lucky.

544
00:36:36,027 --> 00:36:38,763
- How much did you win?
- 110,000. Please take this as payment.

545
00:36:38,829 --> 00:36:40,898
If you just pay up every month,

546
00:36:40,965 --> 00:36:43,467
- it would make all our lives easier.
- I'm sorry.

547
00:36:44,001 --> 00:36:45,169
<i>Are you in debt?</i>

548
00:36:47,772 --> 00:36:49,607
And are you involved
with any shady people?

549
00:36:50,675 --> 00:36:51,842
I can report you.

550
00:36:57,481 --> 00:36:59,350
I understand. I'll go tell my superiors.

551
00:36:59,417 --> 00:37:01,686
Fine, I got it! I'll do as you say!

552
00:37:11,162 --> 00:37:12,697
Naoto!

553
00:37:13,431 --> 00:37:15,366
- It's me.
- Junichi.

554
00:37:19,070 --> 00:37:20,037
I want to talk.

555
00:37:20,571 --> 00:37:23,307
- Is this allowed?
- If I get caught, I'll be in trouble.

556
00:37:25,343 --> 00:37:28,546
I asked you when you took the gun
from the time capsule.

557
00:37:29,146 --> 00:37:30,114
Yeah.

558
00:37:30,181 --> 00:37:31,449
Then you said…

559
00:37:33,184 --> 00:37:35,086
The night I returned from
the business trip to Korea.

560
00:37:37,288 --> 00:37:39,890
So that's Saturday night,
the night of the incident?

561
00:37:40,691 --> 00:37:41,525
Yeah.

562
00:37:42,093 --> 00:37:43,661
What about that?

563
00:37:44,395 --> 00:37:46,364
That story just doesn't add up.

564
00:37:46,998 --> 00:37:47,898
What do you mean?

565
00:37:48,633 --> 00:37:51,002
On Friday night,
the day before the incident,

566
00:37:53,604 --> 00:37:55,306
Keisuke dug up the time capsule.

567
00:37:57,608 --> 00:38:00,144
But he said the gun was already gone
at that time.

568
00:38:00,645 --> 00:38:04,715
But you're saying that you dug it up
and took out the gun on Saturday.

569
00:38:06,584 --> 00:38:09,920
The gun that wasn't there on Friday night
was there on Saturday night?

570
00:38:12,156 --> 00:38:13,124
Naoto,

571
00:38:15,359 --> 00:38:18,596
did you really dig up that time capsule
on Saturday night?

572
00:38:25,369 --> 00:38:28,306
If one of us is lying,

573
00:38:32,109 --> 00:38:33,611
who will you believe?

574
00:38:38,783 --> 00:38:41,085
Of course, you'll believe Keisuke, right?

575
00:38:41,152 --> 00:38:43,554
Hey, I never said that.

576
00:38:44,355 --> 00:38:47,358
Keisuke was an honor student
ever since he was little.

577
00:38:50,027 --> 00:38:51,095
But you know,

578
00:38:54,165 --> 00:38:55,399
back when we were young,

579
00:38:57,001 --> 00:38:59,136
the person I wanted to be

580
00:39:01,238 --> 00:39:03,174
was you, Junichi.

581
00:39:06,077 --> 00:39:07,078
<i>The other day,</i>

582
00:39:07,778 --> 00:39:10,047
<i>when I met you again after a long time,</i>

583
00:39:12,316 --> 00:39:15,519
I thought, "Yes, this is the Junichi
that I always admired."

584
00:39:16,020 --> 00:39:16,987
Hey,

585
00:39:17,588 --> 00:39:19,523
what kind of a weird confession is this?

586
00:39:20,291 --> 00:39:21,926
Do you understand the situation you're in?

587
00:39:26,831 --> 00:39:28,299
After the graduation ceremony,

588
00:39:31,068 --> 00:39:34,338
we buried a time capsule
that would never be dug up again.

589
00:39:37,508 --> 00:39:41,479
<i>You and Keisuke moved to Yokohama,</i>

590
00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:44,315
<i>so Maki and I were the ones left behind.</i>

591
00:39:46,117 --> 00:39:48,586
<i>But Maki also moved away</i>
<i>when she was in high school,</i>

592
00:39:50,988 --> 00:39:52,656
leaving me alone.

593
00:39:56,127 --> 00:39:57,128
I…

594
00:40:00,698 --> 00:40:03,100
felt that I should never leave this town.

595
00:40:05,503 --> 00:40:07,171
I felt like

596
00:40:07,738 --> 00:40:09,473
I had to watch over that time capsule.

597
00:40:10,608 --> 00:40:12,743
I thought that was my duty.

598
00:40:16,480 --> 00:40:18,048
It's no exaggeration.

599
00:40:19,984 --> 00:40:21,452
I seriously believed it.

600
00:40:25,456 --> 00:40:28,359
Later, Maki and Keisuke

601
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:31,762
got married and returned to this town.

602
00:40:36,100 --> 00:40:37,101
I never thought

603
00:40:37,968 --> 00:40:40,538
you would come back here too.

604
00:40:45,843 --> 00:40:46,911
Is it true

605
00:40:47,778 --> 00:40:51,048
that when you're ordered to transfer
to another department, you can't refuse?

606
00:40:51,916 --> 00:40:54,618
I couldn't,
but I also had no reason to either.

607
00:40:55,953 --> 00:40:56,887
Is that so?

608
00:40:59,123 --> 00:41:00,124
I thought

609
00:41:01,859 --> 00:41:04,261
you would never

610
00:41:05,262 --> 00:41:07,531
come back here again.

611
00:41:09,400 --> 00:41:10,334
Why?

612
00:41:21,145 --> 00:41:23,113
Why aren't you married, Junichi?

613
00:41:28,018 --> 00:41:29,920
There's no particular reason.

614
00:41:32,890 --> 00:41:34,692
Besides, I don't feel the need to.

615
00:41:34,758 --> 00:41:36,393
Why didn't you contact Maki

616
00:41:38,529 --> 00:41:40,431
after we all graduated?

617
00:41:41,298 --> 00:41:43,934
That's how most middle schoolers are.

618
00:41:50,674 --> 00:41:53,077
Isn't it because
you were shouldering something

619
00:41:55,312 --> 00:41:58,282
- that you'll never be able to escape from?
- Hey,

620
00:41:58,782 --> 00:42:00,885
- what are you talking about?
- I too…

621
00:42:04,889 --> 00:42:07,057
have something I've been shouldering.

622
00:42:10,060 --> 00:42:11,529
There's something I've decided

623
00:42:12,696 --> 00:42:14,098
to keep locked away in my heart

624
00:42:15,699 --> 00:42:17,001
for the rest of my life.

625
00:42:23,240 --> 00:42:24,842
You have something like that too, right?

626
00:42:27,778 --> 00:42:28,979
But you know,

627
00:42:31,315 --> 00:42:32,716
I think it's okay now.

628
00:42:35,686 --> 00:42:37,621
It's okay to be freed from what you did

629
00:42:38,889 --> 00:42:40,357
23 years ago.

630
00:42:40,925 --> 00:42:43,027
What the heck are you talking about?

631
00:42:46,764 --> 00:42:47,731
On that day…

632
00:42:50,234 --> 00:42:51,702
I saw it…

633
00:42:53,604 --> 00:42:54,638
<i>I'll go check things out.</i>

634
00:42:56,006 --> 00:42:57,041
You stay here.

635
00:42:57,107 --> 00:42:58,309
I'll go too.

636
00:42:59,043 --> 00:43:00,077
Don't overdo it.

637
00:44:12,950 --> 00:44:13,784
NEW CRIME IS REVEALED

638
00:44:13,851 --> 00:44:15,119
<i>Why did you become a police officer?</i>

639
00:44:15,185 --> 00:44:16,520
<i>I wasn't supposed to become one.</i>

640
00:44:16,587 --> 00:44:17,921
Because I've committed a crime.

641
00:44:17,988 --> 00:44:19,723
<i>Can you please</i>
<i>come with me to the station?</i>

642
00:44:19,790 --> 00:44:22,760
<i>The key to solving this case is that gun.</i>

643
00:44:22,826 --> 00:44:24,194
<i>Who shot Oshima?</i>

644
00:44:24,261 --> 00:44:27,898
For example,
the first person who arrived at the scene.

645
00:44:27,965 --> 00:44:28,866
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
